history.content:
151 is a deep mix of 40 / 16B level circuits and 61C low level material (logic, architecture). Labs are done in pairs. 

Lecture workload is comparable to 61C. Labs ramp up during the semester, from 'finish in the lab time' to 'lot of independent time'.

Taking those two together as your only upper divs is fine. I would not recommend taking more than 1 additional class.

How is the workload for the class? Are labs done individually? Does it mainly draw from 61C knowledge?

How reasonable would it be to take 151 with 170 if those are the only two upper divs I take?
history.subject: What is 151 like?
